==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sinusoid
<hw>Si"nus*oid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Sinus</ets> +
<ets>-oid</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Geom.)</fld> <def>The curve whose
ordinates are proportional to the sines of the abscissas, the equation
of the curve being <mathex>y = a sin x</mathex>. It is also called the
<altname>curve of sines</altname>.</def><-- pref. sine curve -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sinusoidal</ent>⟦br⟧
